WEBVTT

00:02.263 --> 00:04.265
There they are.
How'd the job go?

00:04.308 --> 00:06.571
Well, we were
in a cold warehouse

00:06.615 --> 00:08.051
guarding
fitness equipment.

00:08.095 --> 00:09.531
How do you think
it went?Ah.

00:09.574 --> 00:11.750
There were no chairs,
so we had to sit on buckets.

00:11.794 --> 00:13.100
And mine broke.

00:13.143 --> 00:16.059
Told you
to double it up.Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:16.103 --> 00:18.279
Fellas, I was just
making small talk.

00:18.322 --> 00:21.412
I don't really care.

00:21.456 --> 00:23.284
Where's, uh...

00:23.327 --> 00:24.415
Where's Vanessa?

00:24.459 --> 00:25.460
She's at FedEx.

00:25.503 --> 00:26.722
Oh, by the way,

00:26.765 --> 00:28.289
she has a birthday
coming up this Saturday.

00:28.332 --> 00:29.638
Oh, boy,
I almost forgot.

00:29.681 --> 00:30.769
You didforget.

00:30.813 --> 00:32.858
That's why I put
some ideas together.

00:32.902 --> 00:34.425
All right,
check this out.

00:34.469 --> 00:36.906
A cop comes in,
right?

00:36.949 --> 00:39.561
Everyone looks around,
confused, scared.

00:39.604 --> 00:40.736
And then, boom!

00:40.779 --> 00:41.954
Out of the blue,

00:41.998 --> 00:44.740
"Officer Goodbody"
tears off his uniform,

00:44.783 --> 00:45.871
and he starts to dance,

00:45.915 --> 00:47.569
making his butt cheeks
go like this.

00:47.612 --> 00:49.614
[ Beatboxing ]

00:53.357 --> 00:56.056
What else you got?

00:56.099 --> 00:58.275
Uh, ice-cream cake
and a two-liter bottle of soda.

00:58.319 --> 00:59.668
Done!

00:59.711 --> 01:02.149
Uh, you know you gotta do
more than that, right?

01:02.192 --> 01:04.542
Don't you remember when
we were on the force --

01:04.586 --> 01:06.544
Vanessa made a huge deal
about her birthday?

01:06.588 --> 01:08.807
Yeah. It's like,
"I get it, all right?

01:08.851 --> 01:12.246
You were born.
Let it go."

01:12.289 --> 01:13.812
Maybe we should
plan a party --

01:13.856 --> 01:15.249
deck the whole
place out,

01:15.292 --> 01:16.554
you know,
make it special.

01:16.598 --> 01:18.556
Or we go
with Rootger's idea --

01:18.600 --> 01:21.081
ice-cream cake and a bottle of
soda, and I'm gonna say this --

01:21.124 --> 01:23.779
I don't even think we
need to the bottle of
soda, to be honest.

01:23.822 --> 01:25.737
Hey!
Hey!Hey!
Hey!

01:25.781 --> 01:26.956
Hi, guys.

01:26.999 --> 01:30.568
Well, somebody's got
a birthday coming up.

01:30.612 --> 01:31.526
What are
you gonna be?

01:31.569 --> 01:34.311
Turning the old 47--
41? 41?

01:34.355 --> 01:35.704
You're 41.
Yes.

01:35.747 --> 01:37.488
But we're just gonna treat it
like any other day.

01:37.532 --> 01:38.837
[ Chuckles ]

01:38.881 --> 01:40.665
Okay, you don't want a party
or a little gift --

01:40.709 --> 01:42.102
a little
something-something?

01:42.145 --> 01:44.060
Nope.
You're off the hook.

01:45.322 --> 01:46.323
It's a trap, dawg.

01:46.367 --> 01:47.977
Oh, I get what
you're doing here.

01:48.020 --> 01:49.718
Okay, it's one
of those things where

01:49.761 --> 01:51.633
you're saying
you don't want a party,

01:51.676 --> 01:53.548
but, actually,
deep down inside,

01:53.591 --> 01:55.332
you kind of do.
You get that, boys?

01:55.376 --> 01:57.900
So, we're -- we're "not"
planning a party for Vanessa.

01:57.943 --> 01:59.380
[ Chuckles ]

01:59.423 --> 02:04.036
Listen to me now.

02:04.080 --> 02:08.345
I don't want anything,
okay?

02:08.389 --> 02:10.652
I just want to forget
that it's my birthday

02:10.695 --> 02:12.306
and move on
with my life.

02:12.349 --> 02:13.481
Don't read
into that.

02:13.524 --> 02:15.352
That's it, okay?
You got it?

02:17.093 --> 02:18.529
This is a trick, right?
You want a party.

02:18.573 --> 02:20.052
No!

02:23.012 --> 02:24.927
What just
happened here?

02:24.970 --> 02:28.191
Okay, a "My Little Pony"
ice-cream cake

02:28.235 --> 02:29.453
has just been ordered.

02:29.497 --> 02:31.325
Rootger, she just said
she didn't want a party.

02:31.368 --> 02:32.630
Oh, I'll cancel it,
then.

02:32.674 --> 02:34.328
Yeah,
I-I wouldn't do that

02:34.371 --> 02:35.981
because it's probably
a lot of red tape.

02:36.025 --> 02:38.288
You have to go
through the thing.

02:38.332 --> 02:39.420
Actually,
it's just one click.

02:39.463 --> 02:40.725
I know, but it's
probably on the way,

02:40.769 --> 02:41.857
and that wouldn't
be nice to --

02:41.900 --> 02:43.075
No, it hasn't left yet.

02:43.119 --> 02:44.860
But I'm sure
we paid for it, so...Nope.

02:44.903 --> 02:45.904
Okay, why -- why
are you making me

02:45.948 --> 02:46.905
go through this,
Rootger?

02:46.949 --> 02:49.560
I want the cake.

02:49.604 --> 02:54.391
♪ I am not your ordinary guy

02:54.739 --> 02:57.525
H-How do you spell
"boom-shaka-laka"?

02:57.568 --> 02:59.570
Oh, just like
it sounds.

02:59.614 --> 03:02.530
I have no idea.
That's not even a real word!

03:02.573 --> 03:03.792
Why?

03:03.835 --> 03:05.968
It's for Vanessa's card.
Hey, check it out.

03:06.011 --> 03:07.970
"Think you won't have
a great birthday?

03:08.013 --> 03:09.624
You're off your rock-ah.
[rocker]

03:09.667 --> 03:13.584
'Cause it's time to party
like boom-shaka-laka."

03:13.628 --> 03:14.672
It's great, right?

03:14.716 --> 03:16.413
No.

03:16.457 --> 03:18.328
Please tell me that's not
all you got her.

03:18.372 --> 03:21.113
No, no, I got her --
I got her this too.

03:21.157 --> 03:22.114
A gift card to Chili's.

03:22.158 --> 03:23.159
Yep.

03:23.203 --> 03:25.030
That Chale gave you
for Christmas.

03:25.074 --> 03:26.510
Yeah, it's called "re-gifting."

03:26.554 --> 03:27.946
Everybody's doing it now.

03:27.990 --> 03:30.471
Mr. Gable, you took us
to dinner with that.

03:30.514 --> 03:31.689
We ate.
Yeah.

03:31.733 --> 03:33.822
There's still $37.50
on it, okay?

03:33.865 --> 03:35.563
And that goes a long way
at Chili's, all right?

03:35.606 --> 03:36.694
Dad, no!

03:36.738 --> 03:38.261
Vanessa is your
business partner.

03:38.305 --> 03:40.220
And more importantly,
she's a really good friend.

03:40.263 --> 03:41.438
You have to do better.

03:41.482 --> 03:42.787
Believe me, I tried
to throw her a party.

03:42.831 --> 03:44.528
She almost
bit my head off.

03:44.572 --> 03:46.617
Ahh, maybe she's
a little bit sensitive

03:46.661 --> 03:47.705
about getting older.

03:47.749 --> 03:49.664
Ooh.
I didn't think of that.

03:49.707 --> 03:51.492
You know what it is? I always
take this for granted --

03:51.535 --> 03:53.711
how I keep it all
up to code.

03:55.974 --> 03:58.238
Okay, anyway,
no matter how much

03:58.281 --> 04:00.065
Vanessa says
she doesn't want a party,

04:00.109 --> 04:01.110
trust me, she does.

04:01.153 --> 04:02.198
True.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.721
Women will often
use subtext

04:03.765 --> 04:05.854
as a way of expressing
their feelings.

04:05.897 --> 04:07.290
The key is to learn

04:07.334 --> 04:09.597
how to tune into
their frequency.

04:09.640 --> 04:11.729
My dial, for example,

04:11.773 --> 04:15.646
is always set
to radio station K-endra.

04:15.690 --> 04:17.039
[ Imitates radio tuning ]

04:17.082 --> 04:19.563
[ Deepens voice ]
Where it's love all the time.

04:21.435 --> 04:23.654
Time to change
the station, guy.

04:23.698 --> 04:26.440
But you know what?
You're right.

04:26.483 --> 04:27.658
I gotta do something.

04:27.702 --> 04:30.661
I gotta figure it --

04:30.705 --> 04:31.880
My God, let's do
a surprise party.

04:31.923 --> 04:33.011
I'll throw one for her
at Monkey Fist.

04:33.055 --> 04:34.186
Oh, yeah.

04:34.230 --> 04:35.536
We could just decorate it
to the hilt.

04:35.579 --> 04:36.754
Yeah! Ooh, and we can have --
and we can have --

04:36.798 --> 04:38.626
Shamana! No, no,
you're not doing anything.

04:38.669 --> 04:40.628
Okay, this is my baby,
all right?

04:40.671 --> 04:41.672
I'll plan everything.

04:41.716 --> 04:42.673
Dad, no.
Are you sure?

04:42.717 --> 04:44.066
'Cause, you know,
you always say

04:44.109 --> 04:45.459
details aren't
really your thing.

04:45.502 --> 04:46.547
Why don't you
just make a list,

04:46.590 --> 04:47.591
and Chale and I
can knock it off?

04:47.635 --> 04:48.810
I got it all covered.

04:48.853 --> 04:50.202
Okay, well, do you have
the phone numbers

04:50.246 --> 04:52.466
for everyone
she'd like to invite?

04:52.509 --> 04:55.251
Except for that.

04:55.295 --> 04:56.731
Oh, boy.
Uh, you know what?

04:56.774 --> 04:57.775
I'll just -- I'll just
grab her phone.

04:57.819 --> 04:59.255
I'll take 'em from there.

04:59.299 --> 05:01.344
Even easier -- I set up
the servers at Monkey Fist.

05:01.388 --> 05:04.216
I can hack into her account
in a twinkling.

05:04.260 --> 05:05.696
Uh, what?
No.

05:05.740 --> 05:07.611
That is such an invasion of
privacy. You can't do that.

05:07.655 --> 05:09.004
It is.
It really is, yeah.

05:09.047 --> 05:10.397
Uh, no. You're right,
you're right. Sorry.

05:10.440 --> 05:12.312
I just -- I lost my moral
compass for a second.

05:12.355 --> 05:13.400
What is wrong
with you?

05:13.443 --> 05:14.575
I -- I'll think
of something else.

05:14.618 --> 05:15.576
-Yeah, okay.
-Sorry.

05:15.619 --> 05:16.751
Sorry about that,
sweetheart.

05:16.794 --> 05:19.754
You're a --
Start hacking.

05:19.797 --> 05:21.669
♪♪

05:21.712 --> 05:23.410
-Hey, Dad.
-Hey.

05:23.453 --> 05:25.325
Hey, Mr. Gable.

05:27.065 --> 05:28.719
What's going on
with the shirt?

05:28.763 --> 05:30.155
Oh, all my stuff's
in the laundry.

05:30.199 --> 05:32.375
I just borrowed
one of Kendra's.

05:32.419 --> 05:33.985
Okay, well, I'm gonna need
a different shirt

05:34.029 --> 05:37.380
or some acid
for my eyes.

05:37.424 --> 05:40.601
Sorry, I'll -- I'll just go
and put on a dirty one.

05:40.644 --> 05:41.732
Yeah.

05:41.776 --> 05:42.864
Whoa.

05:42.907 --> 05:44.605
All right,
Vanessa's party.

05:44.648 --> 05:47.085
Um, here's what I'm thinking
food-wise.

05:47.129 --> 05:49.827
Oh, okay.
All right.

05:49.871 --> 05:50.959
Cheese pizza.
Uh-huh.

05:51.002 --> 05:52.090
Crackers and cheese.

05:52.134 --> 05:52.874
Yep.

05:52.917 --> 05:54.266
Mozzarella balls.

05:54.310 --> 05:56.399
And cheesecake
for dessert.

05:56.443 --> 05:58.009
Okay, do you see
a pattern here?

05:58.053 --> 06:00.447
Indeed.
Do you?

06:00.490 --> 06:01.709
Everything
has cheese in it.

06:01.752 --> 06:03.058
Yeah,
it's called a theme.

06:03.101 --> 06:04.886
No, it's called
stuff youlike.

06:04.929 --> 06:07.192
That's the theme.

06:07.236 --> 06:09.194
♪♪

06:09.238 --> 06:10.587
-Hey.
-Hey.

06:10.631 --> 06:13.634
I, uh -- I got to talk
to Vanessa about something.

06:13.677 --> 06:14.939
What's the mood
today?

06:14.983 --> 06:16.158
Not great.

06:16.201 --> 06:18.726
I said "Good morning,"
and she said, "Is it?"

06:18.769 --> 06:19.988
And then
she went in there

06:20.031 --> 06:23.948
and started typing --
like, uh, angry typing.

06:23.992 --> 06:25.602
Probably
the birthday thing.

06:25.646 --> 06:27.517
Well, she's a woman
of a certain age.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.389
Her body is starting
to deteriorate.

06:29.432 --> 06:33.480
You know, it's -- it's hard
to hide that with lipstick.

06:33.523 --> 06:35.133
She tries, though.

06:35.177 --> 06:37.962
You didn't say that before you
said "Good morning," did you?

06:38.006 --> 06:39.964
In my head, I said it.

06:40.008 --> 06:41.836
Okay, good, 'cause I'm
throwing her a surprise party

06:41.879 --> 06:42.793
on Saturday,

06:42.837 --> 06:44.316
and I -- I gotta
convince her

06:44.360 --> 06:46.014
to go to dinner with me,
you know, as a -- as a cover.

06:46.057 --> 06:47.929
Oof. What if she
doesn't go for it?

06:47.972 --> 06:50.235
She has to -- I got
a massive deposit down

06:50.279 --> 06:52.629
and decorations
and all that stuff.

06:52.673 --> 06:54.239
I got a cake coming
with her fat face on it.

06:54.283 --> 06:55.632
It's gonna be a fun time,
though.

06:55.676 --> 06:56.720
Gonna be a lot of fun.

06:56.764 --> 06:59.897
Okay, but I would wait
if I were you.

06:59.941 --> 07:02.334
Like I say, she's not
very happy right now.

07:02.378 --> 07:05.207
Oh, please.
I can handle it.

07:06.556 --> 07:07.514
Hey, how's it going?

07:07.557 --> 07:09.690
Good.
Busy.

07:09.733 --> 07:11.431
Cool, cool.

07:11.474 --> 07:13.476
Very cool.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.086
[ Grunts ]
So, I was thinking,

07:15.130 --> 07:17.132
uh, Saturday, maybe we hit
the new steak place

07:17.175 --> 07:18.568
that opened up on 110.

07:18.612 --> 07:20.831
Apparently, they got a ribeye
the size of your head.

07:20.875 --> 07:21.441
[ Chuckles ]

07:21.484 --> 07:23.399
Ha ha.
No.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.706
Saturday is my birthday,
and I told you

07:25.749 --> 07:27.403
I don't want
to do anything.

07:27.447 --> 07:29.013
What?
It's just dinner.

07:29.057 --> 07:30.232
Look, you gotta eat.

07:30.275 --> 07:31.189
If not the steaks,
how about, uh, Chinese?

07:31.233 --> 07:32.364
We'll go to Chin Wa's.

07:32.408 --> 07:33.931
They got dumplings
the size of your fist.

07:33.975 --> 07:36.194
Okay,
the answer is no.

07:36.238 --> 07:38.109
Okay?
I'm sleeping all day.

07:38.153 --> 07:40.372
My friend works
at a pet clinic,

07:40.416 --> 07:41.896
and she's getting me
one of those pills

07:41.939 --> 07:43.811
they give
to nervous puppies.

07:43.854 --> 07:47.902
[ Southern accent ] Mama gonna
go down nice and smooth.

07:47.945 --> 07:50.034
Look, I know
what's going on here.

07:50.078 --> 07:53.429
Birthdays -- look, they get
less fun as you get older.

07:53.473 --> 07:54.909
They just do.
Huh.

07:54.952 --> 07:56.693
But we can't pretend
like they don't happen.

07:56.737 --> 07:58.478
[ Normal voice ] Mm,
well, that's what I've
been trying to do,

07:58.521 --> 08:01.437
but you won't shut up.

08:01.481 --> 08:03.091
Look, my birthday
just reminds me

08:03.134 --> 08:05.006
of all the stuff that
I didn't do in my life.

08:05.049 --> 08:06.224
No house.
No kids.

08:06.268 --> 08:07.965
I've always wanted
to go to Hawaii.

08:08.009 --> 08:09.140
Walk over hot coals.

08:09.184 --> 08:11.273
Sing a duet
with Prince.

08:11.316 --> 08:12.404
It's probably
for the best.

08:12.448 --> 08:14.842
I mean, those coals,
they're crazy hot.

08:14.885 --> 08:19.499
And the Prince thing --
Well, you know.

08:19.542 --> 08:22.502
Hey, the point is,
I am turning 47,

08:22.545 --> 08:24.504
and I'm just...

08:24.547 --> 08:26.201
not where I thought
I would be in my life.

08:26.244 --> 08:28.638
I just don't see many
reasons to celebrate.What? [ Sighs ]

08:28.682 --> 08:30.074
You think
you're the only one

08:30.118 --> 08:31.554
who hasn't done things
that they w--

08:31.598 --> 08:32.555
that they wanted to do?

08:32.599 --> 08:33.861
I mean, I...
[ Scoffs ]

08:33.904 --> 08:35.776
I got a crazy list.
But you know what I do?

08:35.819 --> 08:38.126
I push forward, and that's
what I need you to do.

08:38.169 --> 08:41.782
Okay, so what's
on your bucket list?

08:41.825 --> 08:43.044
It's kind of private.

08:43.087 --> 08:45.002
What? I just told you my stuff.
Tell me yours.

08:45.046 --> 08:47.178
Fine. I always wanted
to see an eagle --

08:47.222 --> 08:49.137
you know, in real life.

08:49.180 --> 08:50.921
An eagle.

08:50.965 --> 08:52.096
How about that?

08:52.140 --> 08:56.231
Well, it can't be that hard
to see a bird.

08:56.274 --> 08:57.754
What else you got?

08:57.798 --> 08:59.147
I always wanted to go
to Statue of Liberty.What?

08:59.190 --> 09:00.844
The Statue of Liberty --
the lady in the harbor.

09:00.888 --> 09:02.106
I know
the lady in the harbor!

09:02.150 --> 09:03.630
I know who
you're talking about.

09:03.673 --> 09:05.022
I'm saying you live
on Long Island!

09:05.066 --> 09:06.241
It's right there!

09:06.284 --> 09:07.938
I've seen it
a bunch of times,

09:07.982 --> 09:10.985
mostly from that karate studio
in Brooklyn.

09:11.028 --> 09:12.769
Remember I was taking lessons
there for the longest time?

09:12.813 --> 09:13.944
[ Sighs ]

09:13.988 --> 09:15.729
Man, when I quit,
I quit out of nowhere,

09:15.772 --> 09:17.513
and I was getting
in wicked-good shape.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.994
I was almost able to do like
a split between two chairs.

09:20.037 --> 09:21.125
Like Van Damme.

09:21.169 --> 09:22.387
You ever see Van Damme
in the movies

09:22.431 --> 09:23.911
where he does the splits
as he get down low?

09:23.954 --> 09:25.826
Oh, these splits -- that's
another thing on my list.

09:25.869 --> 09:27.088
Okay, well,
that's not gonna happen.

09:27.131 --> 09:28.916
You can barely pick up
a pencil off the floor.

09:28.959 --> 09:30.134
Okay.

09:30.178 --> 09:31.745
What do you want?
I got a bad back, okay?

09:31.788 --> 09:33.834
But for the rest of me,
I'm like a boneless chicken.

09:33.877 --> 09:35.357
I'm very supple.
Very supple.
Okay.

09:35.400 --> 09:37.185
You know what I want?
To be out of this conversation.

09:37.228 --> 09:39.056
So if going to dinner with you
will shut you up, great!

09:39.100 --> 09:40.449
Let's do dinner
Saturday.

09:40.492 --> 09:41.929
Fine. I love it.
All right.

09:41.972 --> 09:44.235
Uh, y-you want
to do, uh, head steaks

09:44.279 --> 09:45.149
or the, uh,
fist dumplings?

09:45.193 --> 09:46.194
Doesn't matter,
hun.

09:46.237 --> 09:47.848
Pick one.

09:47.891 --> 09:48.892
Fist dumplings.

09:48.936 --> 09:50.111
Nope, not even close.
Head steaks.

09:57.466 --> 10:00.295
You know what?

10:00.338 --> 10:01.296
Forget dinner.

10:01.339 --> 10:03.341
I'm gonna throw myself
a party.

10:03.385 --> 10:05.430
What's that, now?

10:05.474 --> 10:07.650
Yeah, I mean,
you were right.

10:07.694 --> 10:08.999
What am I thinking about?

10:09.043 --> 10:10.522
I mean,
my life is pretty great.

10:10.566 --> 10:13.395
And I should throw myself
a birthday bash.

10:13.438 --> 10:14.483
I never said "great."

10:14.526 --> 10:16.311
I mean, you're -- you're
bumping along,

10:16.354 --> 10:17.486
doing fine.

10:17.529 --> 10:19.140
No! Come on, like,
I've never done it.

10:19.183 --> 10:21.403
Like, you know, I'm gonna
invite all my friends,

10:21.446 --> 10:22.883
rent out a space.

10:22.926 --> 10:26.060
I'll get a signature drink --
a "Cellucci Sunrise."

10:26.103 --> 10:27.191
I love that!
Oh, my God.

10:27.235 --> 10:28.323
And then
I'll get a limo --

10:28.366 --> 10:29.846
Uh, you know,
I-I think it's a bad idea.

10:29.890 --> 10:31.326
First of all,
limos are very dangerous

10:31.369 --> 10:32.719
'cause --
You know why?

10:32.762 --> 10:34.024
The mechanics who work on 'em,
they don't own 'em,

10:34.068 --> 10:35.286
so they don't --
they don't care.

10:35.330 --> 10:36.810
Oh, shut up.
Well, this is gonna be great.

10:36.853 --> 10:38.115
I'm gonna start
planning it.

10:38.159 --> 10:40.204
You know what?
Thank you, Kevin.

10:40.248 --> 10:41.466
You're right.

10:48.648 --> 10:50.258
That went straight
in the crapper.

10:56.177 --> 10:58.179
Let me see if
I got this right --

10:58.222 --> 10:59.484
Vanessa's on her way,
and she's gonna invite us

10:59.528 --> 11:01.965
to a beach party,
but we're supposed to say no?

11:02.009 --> 11:03.619
Yeah. I already called
all her contacts.

11:03.663 --> 11:05.099
They're doing the same thing,
all right?

11:05.142 --> 11:06.840
They're all coming
to my surprise party

11:06.883 --> 11:08.102
that I'm throwing
at Monkey Fist.

11:08.145 --> 11:09.930
But the one at the beach
sounds better.

11:09.973 --> 11:11.061
Okay.

11:11.105 --> 11:12.889
There is no party
at the beach, Mott.

11:12.933 --> 11:15.370
I'm squashing it, all right?
Mine's gonna be awesome.

11:15.413 --> 11:17.546
Besides,
I got Rootger deejaying.

11:17.589 --> 11:18.590
You're a deejay?

11:18.634 --> 11:20.114
Yeah.
Here, I'm Rootger.

11:20.157 --> 11:21.985
But in Holland,
I'm MC Root --

11:22.029 --> 11:23.900
the man who makes
the party...

11:23.944 --> 11:25.206
[ Imitates
record scratching ]

11:25.249 --> 11:27.643
...a wicked-good
time.

11:27.687 --> 11:28.949
Wouldn't it
just be easier

11:28.992 --> 11:30.385
to let Vanessa plan
her own party?

11:30.428 --> 11:31.691
Then you'd be
off the hook.

11:31.734 --> 11:33.518
No. I put in a lot of work
for this, all right?

11:33.562 --> 11:34.737
I-I bought all the food.

11:34.781 --> 11:36.434
I got the decorations
and stuff.

11:36.478 --> 11:38.262
I did all this stuff
out of the kindness of my heart.

11:38.306 --> 11:40.177
I'm getting credit for it.
That's what I'm doing.

11:40.221 --> 11:42.484
I need you guys to just come up
with an excuse, all right?

11:42.527 --> 11:43.485
That's all I'm asking.

11:43.528 --> 11:44.704
Oh, I'm not good
at lying.

11:44.747 --> 11:46.183
I start sweating
like crazy.

11:46.227 --> 11:48.055
Okay, you sweat like crazy
anyway.

11:48.098 --> 11:50.405
You're gonna be fine.
She's not gonna know.

11:50.448 --> 11:52.581
You know, Vanessa tried calling
me three times today, and...

11:52.624 --> 11:55.279
[ Scoffs ] Man, just to see
her face on that screen

11:55.323 --> 11:58.630
and me having to ignore
the call -- tough.

11:58.674 --> 12:00.415
You have a picture of her
on your phone?

12:00.458 --> 12:01.764
Yeah, I took
a quick shot of her

12:01.808 --> 12:04.462
when she dozed off
on Thanksgiving.

12:04.506 --> 12:05.986
All right,
here she comes.

12:06.029 --> 12:06.900
Hey!
Hey!Hey!
Hey!

12:06.943 --> 12:07.857
How's it going?
All right?

12:07.901 --> 12:09.119
Left your phone
at the office.

12:09.163 --> 12:10.468
Oh, thank you.
Hey --You're welcome.

12:10.512 --> 12:11.948
How's the party
planning going?

12:11.992 --> 12:13.210
Oh, my -- Awful.

12:13.254 --> 12:14.690
What?!

12:14.734 --> 12:17.867
Yes, everybody I invited
can't come.

12:17.911 --> 12:19.216
That is
so disappointing.

12:19.260 --> 12:20.652
I-I mean,
I gotta tell you,

12:20.696 --> 12:22.916
we'll -- we'll be there,
right, boys?

12:22.959 --> 12:25.135
Um, actually,
I can't make it.

12:25.179 --> 12:26.876
Didi and I have
a wedding to attend.

12:26.920 --> 12:29.183
-Whaaat?
-I know.

12:29.226 --> 12:30.532
I, uh --
I can't go, either.

12:30.575 --> 12:32.490
[ Quietly ] Oh, God,
it's so hot in here.

12:32.534 --> 12:34.014
Rootger,
what about you?

12:34.057 --> 12:35.145
I'm so sorry.
I can't.

12:35.189 --> 12:37.017
I have to go back
to the doctor.

12:37.060 --> 12:38.366
That thing on my toe
came back.

12:38.409 --> 12:39.236
[ Scoffs ]

12:39.280 --> 12:40.150
What?

12:40.194 --> 12:41.412
You guys
are unbelievable.

12:41.456 --> 12:42.631
Yeah, really!

12:42.674 --> 12:44.459
I mean, it's like,
every time you need me,

12:44.502 --> 12:45.286
I'm there.

12:45.329 --> 12:46.678
Everytime.

12:46.722 --> 12:47.767
And then,

12:47.810 --> 12:49.681
when it's my birthday,
my party...

12:49.725 --> 12:50.900
Yeah....everybody's busy.

12:50.944 --> 12:52.162
Exactly.
You sicken me.

12:52.206 --> 12:55.557
You sicken-a me
to the height of sickenness.

12:55.600 --> 12:56.732
Just unbelievable.

12:56.776 --> 12:57.820
Don't even worry about them.
I'll be there.

12:57.864 --> 12:58.952
Yeah,
not cool, guys.

12:58.995 --> 12:59.866
I'll be there for you, too,
Vanessa.

12:59.909 --> 13:00.780
-Yeah.
-No, no.

13:00.823 --> 13:01.781
Thank you,
but forg--

13:01.824 --> 13:03.130
I'm just gonna
cancel the party.

13:03.173 --> 13:05.132
We'll just go back to
the dinner thing, all right?

13:05.175 --> 13:06.437
I-I guess that's
probably best now.

13:06.481 --> 13:07.961
All right,
I'll see you guys later.

13:08.004 --> 13:08.831
-All right.
-All right.

13:08.875 --> 13:10.398
Geez.

13:10.441 --> 13:11.834
All right,
good job, boys.

13:11.878 --> 13:13.096
You made us look
like idiots.

13:13.140 --> 13:14.532
Not cool, guy.

13:14.576 --> 13:16.230
What, are you sure
you want to do this to her?

13:16.273 --> 13:17.274
Once we all
yell "Surprise,"

13:17.318 --> 13:18.928
all the pain goes away,
all right?

13:18.972 --> 13:21.017
It's exactly like
I did with my kids.

13:21.061 --> 13:22.976
I'd make them think
I forgot their birthday.

13:23.019 --> 13:24.673
And then once they saw
the balloons

13:24.716 --> 13:27.502
and the prizes and stuff,
all good times.

13:27.545 --> 13:29.417
Except that one time
I did actually forget Jack's.

13:29.460 --> 13:30.505
And that was tough.

13:30.548 --> 13:31.854
Technically,
he never turned eight.

13:31.898 --> 13:33.725
Never turned eight.

13:33.769 --> 13:35.162
♪♪

13:35.205 --> 13:36.380
Hey.
Here you go, buddy.

13:36.424 --> 13:38.295
Take that for me.
How it's going, Rootger?

13:38.339 --> 13:39.514
You know the routine?
You got it down?

13:39.557 --> 13:41.298
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Vanessa comes in.

13:41.342 --> 13:44.649
House lights go up.
Then we all yell "Surprise!"

13:44.693 --> 13:46.826
I hit the music, and then
I hit the light show.

13:46.869 --> 13:47.609
Okay.

13:47.652 --> 13:48.784
Light show?

13:48.828 --> 13:50.699
[ Chuckling ] Oh!

13:50.742 --> 13:53.571
Ha-ha!
Light show, baby!

13:53.615 --> 13:55.399
Whoo!All right, all right,
all right, all right, all right.

13:55.443 --> 13:58.576
Turn it off,
Deejay Lite-Brite.

13:58.620 --> 14:00.187
Ah, way to suck out
the fun.

14:00.230 --> 14:01.884
Come on!
Hi, Dad.

14:01.928 --> 14:03.581
Uh, so, guests are gonna
start arriving any minute.

14:03.625 --> 14:04.931
Maybe you should
go pick up Vanessa.

14:04.974 --> 14:06.889
No, it's -- it's okay.
I got Kyle getting her.

14:06.933 --> 14:08.325
I wanted to make sure
everything was in order

14:08.369 --> 14:09.761
over here.Wait, what?

14:09.805 --> 14:11.198
No, I thought you were
taking her to dinner

14:11.241 --> 14:12.808
and then bringing her here
yourself.

14:12.852 --> 14:15.332
It's okay. I told Kyle to tell
her that my car broke down.

14:15.376 --> 14:17.204
Oh, crafty lie,
Mr. Gable.

14:17.247 --> 14:19.162
Using your brother
as a little misdirection.

14:19.206 --> 14:20.598
Mm, exactly.

14:20.642 --> 14:22.209
No, Dad.

14:22.252 --> 14:23.427
What if she gets
really upset,

14:23.471 --> 14:24.515
and she's gonna think
that you ditched her,

14:24.559 --> 14:25.516
and then,
if she just goes home,

14:25.560 --> 14:26.866
this entire thing
is ruined.

14:26.909 --> 14:27.779
Okay, relax,
all right?

14:27.823 --> 14:28.737
The guy's
messed up a lot,

14:28.780 --> 14:31.044
but even Kyle
can handle this.

14:31.087 --> 14:32.306
♪♪

14:32.349 --> 14:34.351
So, first, nobody wanted
to come to my party,

14:34.395 --> 14:37.398
and now your brother --
the only friend I have left --

14:37.441 --> 14:38.921
stands me up.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.923
[ Scoffs ]

14:40.967 --> 14:41.924
You know,
I think I'm just --

14:41.968 --> 14:42.838
I'm just gonna go home.

14:42.882 --> 14:43.926
I'm gonna just go.No, no.

14:43.970 --> 14:44.971
No, he --
h-he'll be here.

14:45.014 --> 14:45.885
-Okay --
-Trust me.

14:45.928 --> 14:47.103
He's over an hour
late.

14:47.147 --> 14:48.409
Obviously, it's not
that important to him.

14:48.452 --> 14:49.410
It is.
It is.

14:49.453 --> 14:50.759
It isn't!
I mean, it really --

14:50.802 --> 14:52.065
It just stings
when you realize,

14:52.108 --> 14:53.457
like, you really are
alone in the world.

14:53.501 --> 14:54.894
Yeah, I know.
I know.

14:54.937 --> 14:56.852
[ Chuckles ]
I-I feel the same way.

14:56.896 --> 14:59.072
All the time.

14:59.115 --> 15:01.291
See, Kyle,
you do get it.

15:01.335 --> 15:03.424
All right, well,
then here's to life

15:03.467 --> 15:04.686
sucking
a bowl of lemons.

15:04.729 --> 15:07.515
Ah, salud!
Salud.

15:07.558 --> 15:08.951
Mm.
[ Smacks lips ]

15:08.995 --> 15:10.822
You know, I always thought
I was better than you,

15:10.866 --> 15:14.435
and...the truth is,
I'm -- I'm really not.

15:14.478 --> 15:16.306
But -- But you are
better than me.A little bit.

15:16.350 --> 15:18.395
A little bit,
but not a ton.

15:18.439 --> 15:20.876
Not a ton
that I thought.

15:20.920 --> 15:23.487
But you are here celebrating
my birthday with me,

15:23.531 --> 15:24.271
so thank you.

15:24.314 --> 15:25.750
You're welcome.

15:25.794 --> 15:28.275
You know, if you --
if you turn your head

15:28.318 --> 15:30.233
slightly
towards the light

15:30.277 --> 15:31.408
and the light hits you
just right --

15:31.452 --> 15:36.152
and it has to hit you
justright...

15:36.196 --> 15:38.981
you're actually
kind of cute.

15:39.025 --> 15:40.330
What's, uh...

15:40.374 --> 15:42.376
W-What's -- What's
going on here?

15:42.419 --> 15:45.379
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

15:45.422 --> 15:46.554
Is that Kevin?

15:46.597 --> 15:48.208
I don't know
who that is.

15:54.040 --> 15:56.172
Look, I don't -- I don't
know where this is going,

15:56.216 --> 15:58.218
but if we do kiss,
full transparency,

15:58.261 --> 16:00.611
I have a wicked
nose whistle.

16:00.655 --> 16:02.004
Kiss?
We're not gonna kiss.

16:02.048 --> 16:04.180
And it's not because
of a nose whistle.

16:04.224 --> 16:06.139
Is it my bulgy eyes?
'Cause I'll have them fixed.

16:06.182 --> 16:08.358
No! Stop it!
It's not your eyes.

16:08.402 --> 16:09.664
[ Sighs ]
Well, what is it, then?

16:09.707 --> 16:11.057
I-I want to get back
to that moment.

16:11.100 --> 16:12.101
Tell me.
I'll do anything.

16:12.145 --> 16:13.276
Kyle,
it wasn't anything.

16:13.320 --> 16:14.799
What are you doing?Oh, not now, guy.

16:14.843 --> 16:16.888
We're in the middle of something
here, huh? Take a lap.

16:16.932 --> 16:18.629
No, we are not in the middle
of anything!

16:18.673 --> 16:21.415
Ugh!
Unbelievable.

16:21.458 --> 16:23.199
Look, uh, come on.
We -- We got to go.

16:23.243 --> 16:24.418
The alarm went off
at Money Fist,

16:24.461 --> 16:25.375
and I want to make sure
everything's --

16:25.419 --> 16:26.855
Oh, really? Okay.Okay. Yes.

16:26.898 --> 16:29.031
You and Rootger handle it, okay?
I'm just gonna go home.

16:29.075 --> 16:30.250
No, I need you.You need me?

16:30.293 --> 16:31.425
I just want
this day to end.

16:31.468 --> 16:32.643
It's been one of the worst
days of my life.

16:32.687 --> 16:34.384
So, I-I didn't forget
your birthday, okay?

16:34.428 --> 16:36.038
I sent Kyle in here
to keep you busy

16:36.082 --> 16:39.607
so you wouldn't
ruin the surprise.

16:39.650 --> 16:40.782
Surprise?

16:40.825 --> 16:42.088
[ Sighing ] Yes.

16:42.131 --> 16:43.654
Look, I've been planning
this thing for a week.

16:43.698 --> 16:46.005
I wanted to do something special
for your birthday, that's all.

16:46.048 --> 16:48.094
Wait. So, you had
my friends cancel on me?

16:48.137 --> 16:50.444
I did.

16:50.487 --> 16:53.055
Okay, do you know how
devastating that could've been?

16:53.099 --> 16:54.404
All right, what do --
[ Sighs ]

16:54.448 --> 16:55.318
I'm sorry.

16:55.362 --> 16:57.059
I-I-I just
wanted to do...

16:57.103 --> 16:58.278
something special
for your birthday.

16:58.321 --> 16:59.453
That's all.

16:59.496 --> 17:02.064
Oh, wow, you really
threw me a party?

17:02.108 --> 17:04.371
Yes! And -- And
everybody's waiting.

17:04.414 --> 17:06.938
So, come on,
let's go!

17:06.982 --> 17:08.418
I got it.
Is it my teeth?

17:08.462 --> 17:10.594
Because if it is, don't worry.
They're not even mine.

17:10.638 --> 17:11.900
These babies
pop right out.

17:11.943 --> 17:13.467
You know, it's like
a one-piece bridge.

17:13.510 --> 17:15.164
Click-click, gone.

17:20.039 --> 17:22.041
Looks like Rootger forgot
to leave the lights on.

17:22.084 --> 17:22.998
Yeah.

17:23.042 --> 17:25.348
Together: Surprise!

17:25.392 --> 17:26.610
What?!

17:26.654 --> 17:29.309
I am so surprised!

17:29.352 --> 17:31.006
This is me
so surprised!

17:31.050 --> 17:33.443
Uh, take it -- take it
down a notch.

17:33.487 --> 17:35.793
Little less ham
on that sandwich, okay?

17:35.837 --> 17:38.144
Well, thank you,
everybody!

17:38.187 --> 17:39.014
Hi!

17:39.058 --> 17:40.102
Oh, this is so sweet.

17:40.146 --> 17:41.060
Thank you.Ah.

17:41.103 --> 17:41.973
It's what
partners do.

17:42.017 --> 17:42.800
-Aww!
-All right?

17:42.844 --> 17:44.150
All right.[ Chuckles ]

17:44.193 --> 17:45.934
Ah!

17:45.977 --> 17:48.371
For you!Oh, you're so sweet.

17:48.415 --> 17:49.807
-Hey!
-Hey!

17:49.851 --> 17:53.898
A Cellucci Sunrise
for the birthday girl!

17:53.942 --> 17:57.772
Oh, you remembered.
Thank you so much.

17:57.815 --> 17:59.556
Oh, my gosh.

17:59.600 --> 18:01.036
[ Slurps ]

18:01.080 --> 18:02.298
I'll take
another one.

18:02.342 --> 18:04.953
Oh. [ Chuckles ]
Already?

18:04.996 --> 18:08.217
I got seven kids and a giant
husband with sleep apnea.

18:08.261 --> 18:11.220
Every night, he straps that mask
on his big, fat face,

18:11.264 --> 18:13.353
giant cheeks falling
out the sides,

18:13.396 --> 18:14.876
snoring and vibrating.

18:14.919 --> 18:20.316
Bottom line --
This glass never gets empty.

18:22.057 --> 18:26.931
Well, I guess I can cross
Hawaii off my bucket list!

18:26.975 --> 18:28.977
Well, there's actually
something else

18:29.020 --> 18:29.978
you can cross off.

18:30.021 --> 18:32.981
Antonio Banderas
is here?

18:33.024 --> 18:34.765
Yeah, no.
I wish.
Oh.

18:34.809 --> 18:36.115
Okay, Rootger,
hit it.

18:36.158 --> 18:38.334
Oh.
What's going on?

18:38.378 --> 18:40.989
[ Slow-tempo music playing ]

18:41.032 --> 18:44.514
♪ Mm, never meant
to cause you any sorrow ♪

18:47.038 --> 18:52.783
♪ Mm, never meant
to cause you any pain ♪

18:54.872 --> 19:02.228
♪ I only want to see you dancing
in that purple rain ♪

19:02.271 --> 19:04.186
Together:
♪ Purple rain

19:04.230 --> 19:06.014
♪ Purple rain

19:06.057 --> 19:10.671
♪♪

19:10.714 --> 19:12.629
♪ Purple rain

19:12.673 --> 19:15.328
♪ Purple rain

19:17.939 --> 19:24.728
♪ I only want to see you
laughing in the purple rain ♪

19:24.772 --> 19:27.601
♪ Purple --
♪ Come on,
come on, come on ♪

19:27.644 --> 19:29.994
♪ At the monkey fist

19:30.038 --> 19:31.953
[ Mouthing "Oh, wow.
Okay" ]

19:33.781 --> 19:36.958
♪ Vanessa's birthday

19:37.001 --> 19:41.528
♪ Well, Kevin Gable
pulled it off ♪

19:41.571 --> 19:44.922
♪ She's 47

19:44.966 --> 19:46.228
♪ 41

19:46.272 --> 19:48.883
♪ Sorry about
that part ♪

19:48.926 --> 19:50.841
♪ Mm-hmm

19:50.885 --> 19:53.931
♪♪

19:53.975 --> 19:55.411
Whoo!

19:55.455 --> 19:57.413
[ Claps ]

19:58.719 --> 20:00.286
Whew.

20:00.329 --> 20:01.330
Powerful.

20:09.904 --> 20:14.735
[ Pensive music playing ]

20:14.778 --> 20:16.302
[ Exhales ]

20:16.345 --> 20:19.392
[ Straining ] Bucket list
almost complete.

20:19.435 --> 20:20.393
[ Eagle chirps ]

20:20.436 --> 20:24.788
♪♪

20:24.832 --> 20:27.008
[ Grunts ]

20:27.051 --> 20:33.014
♪♪

20:33.057 --> 20:36.496
Bucket list complete.

20:36.539 --> 20:39.194
Hoo-ahh.

20:39.238 --> 20:44.939
♪♪

20:44.982 --> 20:48.159
♪ Don't want no sweet perfume

20:48.203 --> 20:51.772
♪ Shake your thing,
go bust your move ♪

20:51.815 --> 20:53.426
♪ Do, do, do, do, do

20:53.469 --> 20:55.428
♪ Do, do, do, do

20:55.471 --> 20:58.953
♪ Ohhhhhh, yeah

20:58.996 --> 21:01.825
♪ Don't want
no high-heel shoes ♪

